Use this command to turn off DPMS:

    xset -dpms</description><pubDate>Tue, 09 Jul 2013 18:20:51 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/2134/screen-turns-black/?answer=2164#post-id-2164</guid></item><item><title>Comment by Pinyaka for &lt;p&gt;Sounds like DPMS, a power-saving technique.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Use this command to turn off DPMS:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;xset -dpms
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
</title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/2134/screen-turns-black/?comment=3394#comment-3394</link><description>There is a bug in dpms with the kde that ships with Debian Wheezy that allows dpms to turn back on regularly, so if you end up doing this, you may need to add this to your crontab and have it run every 5-10 minutes.</description><pubDate>Thu, 13 Feb 2014 19:29:52 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/2134/screen-turns-black/?comment=3394#comment-3394</guid></item></channel></rss>